The **Accounts **panel allows to view and edit existing accounts, and to create new ones.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Creating an account
- Click **Add**. The **Create Account **form is displayed.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Enter the following details (mandatory fields are marked with an asterisk *):

**Section**

**Field**

**Mandatory**

**Description**

**General Information**

**Account name**

X

Name of the account (a combination of alphanumeric characters, spaces, and special characters)

**Salesforce Case**

Number of the Salesforce case linked to the creation of the account

**Profiles**

Select the profile(s) to associate with the account.

> Note

Batch and On-Demand profiles determine which tasks can be used to design workflows.

> Important

Only one profile per type may be associated with an account. It is not possible to associate multiple profiles of the same type.

**Tags**

**Tags**

Enter one or more tags (up to 10 tags, separated by a comma) to label the account. Tags may have a maximum length of 20 characters.

- Click **Save **to confirm.

### Viewing the details of an account
Click on the name of an account to view its details.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Note

For more information on how to edit an account, see [Editing an account](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-accounts#editing-an-account) below.

> Note

The **History **panel lists all changes performed on the account, including the status icon, date and time, and name of the user who performed the action.

### Editing an account
- Click on the name of an account to view its details.

or:

Select the account that you want to modify and click **Edit**.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Edit the required information.

> Note

For more information on the available fields, see [Creating an account](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-accounts#creating-an-account) above.

- Click **Update **to confirm.

> Tip

If you make any changes to the account details and then click on a different tab or the **Back **browser button, the system displays the following prompt, allowing you to save, discard, or cancel the changes.
